        advanced: 'Create comprehensive locale selector. Trigger variants: dropdown button, icon-only button (for headers), inline select, footer link format. Display options: flag + native name, flag + English name, native name only (flags can be controversial). Language list: ISO language codes, native language names, completion percentage for partial translations. Grouping: popular/common languages at top, then alphabetical, or by region. Search: filter languages by name (in any language), keyboard navigation through filtered results. Selection: current language highlighted, persist choice in cookie/localStorage and user preferences. URL strategy: subdomain (en.site.com), path prefix (/en/page), query param (?lang=en), or domain per region. Detection: auto-detect from browser language, suggest switch if different from current. RTL support: automatically switch to RTL layout for Arabic, Hebrew, etc. Currency/region: optional region selector alongside language (affects currency, date format). Incomplete translations: warning badge if language has incomplete translations, fallback language display. Keyboard shortcut: configurable shortcut to open language selector. Flags: use flag icons carefully, some users find them inaccurate (e.g., UK flag for English used by US users). Accessibility: proper button/menu semantics, language names in native script, live region announcement on change.'
